summary: Diana N Jones is identified as an employee of the U.S. House of Representatives Select Committee on Assassinations (HSCA) based on payroll certifications from October 1977, November 1977, and May 1978. The documents list her name alongside other committee staff, indicating she was likely involved in the HSCA's investigation into the JFK assassination. The payroll certifications provide information about her position and salary during the specified periods, but do not offer specific details about her role within the committee or her direct involvement in the JFK assassination investigation.
significance: Diana N Jones' significance lies in her employment with the House Select Committee on Assassinations, suggesting her involvement in the investigation of the JFK assassination.
